00:12:04,767 --> 00:12:08,433
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

259
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:11,400
He thinks Charleston
is behind the hacking incident.

260
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:15,400
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

261
00:12:15,567 --> 00:12:16,467
What?

262
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:20,100
Has he gone mad?

263
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:26,333
[GINA] Wilson,
I love this place.

264
00:12:26,467 --> 00:12:28,533
Is Cindy busy now?

265
00:12:28,667 --> 00:12:31,933
It's been a while since
I've had you all to myself.

266
00:12:32,067 --> 00:12:35,100
You know, while sharing
some wine,

267
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:38,667
this nice ambience,
and good food.

268
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:41,633
Thank you for taking me
out on a date,

269
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:43,100
with just the two of us.

270
00:12:43,967 --> 00:12:45,467
This is not a date.

271
00:12:45,633 --> 00:12:47,267
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

272
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:48,500
[CARLO] Ma! Pa!

273
00:12:49,933 --> 00:12:51,000
Hi, Ma!

274
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:52,633
[SMOOCHES]

275
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:54,367
Pa.

276
00:12:56,067 --> 00:12:57,133
[GINA] Still...

277
00:12:58,167 --> 00:12:59,633
It's a family date.

278
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:06,567
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

279
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:10,300
I thought our families
were okay now.

280
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:13,833
Edward only said that to get
back at your brother.

281
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,233
No, Ma.

282
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:19,667
I mean, it's possible, right?

283
00:13:20,533 --> 00:13:22,333
Charleston was gone
for some time.

284
00:13:22,533 --> 00:13:24,667
What if he's doing this
to spite Papa?

285
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:26,267
We don't even
know the reason

286
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:29,100
why he suddenly came
back from America.

287
00:13:29,233 --> 00:13:32,100
So are you saying you'd
rather trust Edward

288
00:13:32,233 --> 00:13:33,700
than your brother?

289
00:13:33,867 --> 00:13:36,000
Of course not, Ma.

290
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:38,167
You know how much
I love Charleston.

291
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:41,233
That's why I want to catch
the culprit.

292
00:13:41,367 --> 00:13:43,067
I'll prove
Edward wrong

293
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:44,700
and make him regret
his words.

294
00:13:46,967 --> 00:13:48,033
[BETTINA] I just...

295
00:13:49,367 --> 00:13:51,400
I just really hope
he's wrong about it.

296
00:13:51,533 --> 00:13:52,767
He is, Bettina.

297
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:54,000
He's wrong.

298
00:13:55,233 --> 00:13:56,600
How sure are we, Ma?

299
00:13:58,233 --> 00:14:01,067
Like I said, Charleston
was gone for some time.

300
00:14:02,167 --> 00:14:04,633
- Do we know him like before?
- Yes, I know him!

301
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:07,633
He's my son, so I know
him well.

302
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:11,700
He'd never do that
to your father.

303
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:15,633
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:14:15,767 --> 00:14:18,367
Have you added
the sesame oil?

305
00:14:19,667 --> 00:14:20,700
[BETTINA] Yeah, I did.

306
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:26,600
[GINA] Son, I'm so happy
you joined us tonight.

307
00:14:26,733 --> 00:14:29,600
I'm glad Papa included me
in this business meeting.

308
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:31,733
[WILSON] No worries.

309
00:14:32,433 --> 00:14:34,067
How are things
in the office?

310
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:35,933
The OPIP proposal
was rejected.

311
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:37,233
What?

312
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:41,567
Caroline rejected
the person who saved her

313
00:14:41,700 --> 00:14:42,567
and her hero?

314
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:45,733
That's not only sad.

315
00:14:45,833 --> 00:14:47,067
That's cruel.

316
00:14:47,867 --> 00:14:50,767
Well, she did it in a very
professional manner.

317
00:14:50,933 --> 00:14:52,233
All her points are valid.

318
00:14:55,300 --> 00:14:57,433
If Caroline had approved
the project proposal

319
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:59,267
just because she feels
indebted,

320
00:15:00,467 --> 00:15:03,567
I don't think Bingo would feel
triumphant about it.

321
00:15:05,233 --> 00:15:06,367
[CARLO] Mm-hmm.

322
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:08,667
Besides, if you think
about it,

323
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:11,000
Ling gave him
a chance

324
00:15:11,133 --> 00:15:13,133
even though someone else
was chosen for the grant.

325
00:15:13,967 --> 00:15:15,367
[WILSON] That's how it is, son.

326
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:18,433
You'll receive lots of no's
in the business.

327
00:15:19,233 --> 00:15:23,033
And before you even
hear that sweet "yes,"

328
00:15:23,167 --> 00:15:24,767
you shouldn't give up.

329
00:15:26,067 --> 00:15:28,333
That's what I want
in that young man.

330
00:15:29,567 --> 00:15:33,033
He has perseverance
and grit.

331
00:15:33,167 --> 00:15:40,433
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

332
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:41,467
[GINA] Let's eat.

333
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:45,133
I won't give up.

334
00:15:45,267 --> 00:15:47,733
If they don't like OPIP,
then I'll try other companies.

335
00:15:47,867 --> 00:15:48,867
That's the spirit.

336
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:51,500
I'll sell it to those
who want it.

337
00:15:51,667 --> 00:15:52,800
That's more like it.

338
00:15:52,967 --> 00:15:56,000
You'll just end up getting hurt
if you force yourself on others.

339
00:15:56,167 --> 00:15:58,033
Find someone who
will accept you too.

340
00:15:58,167 --> 00:15:59,967
Once they see
the project succeed,

341
00:16:00,067 --> 00:16:01,633
they'll regret their decision.

342
00:16:02,667 --> 00:16:04,400
That's how life is.

343
00:16:04,533 --> 00:16:07,833
We should just move on
and find other opportunities.

344
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,033
If we fail,
we just stand up again.

345
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:12,733
Keep repeating that
until you succeed in life.

346
00:16:16,367 --> 00:16:18,200
I just don't get Ling.

347
00:16:19,733 --> 00:16:21,833
It's like your friendship
doesn't mean anything to her.

348
00:16:21,933 --> 00:16:23,267
Exactly.

349
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:30,533
It's a good thing I won't
see that woman again.

350
00:16:33,433 --> 00:16:35,767
[SINGING]
<i> Every shing-a-ling-a-ling</i>

351
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:36,833
[LAUGHS]

352
00:16:36,933 --> 00:16:39,367
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

353
00:16:39,533 --> 00:16:43,567
[SINGING]
<i> Every crazy-ling-a-ling</i>

354
00:16:43,733 --> 00:16:49,233
[LAUGHTER]

355
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:50,967
Let's drink to that!

356
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:52,733
Bottoms up!

357
00:16:52,900 --> 00:16:55,233
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

358
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:56,900
Miss, another round, please.

359
00:16:59,300 --> 00:17:00,600
This tastes weird.

360
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:02,867
[MONCHING SIGHS]

361
00:17:02,967 --> 00:17:04,867
Where is Bingo, Ma?

362
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:08,300
I think he'll be coming
home late.

363
00:17:08,433 --> 00:17:11,233
He called, but he
didn't say much.

364
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:13,600
We didn't talk that long.

365
00:17:13,733 --> 00:17:15,600
What did he say?

366
00:17:15,767 --> 00:17:19,267
He said the OPIP proposal
got rejected.

367
00:17:21,267 --> 00:17:23,767
- Oh, dear.
- That's all he said.

368
00:17:23,933 --> 00:17:26,900
I bet he's in a bad mood.
Anyway, let him be.

369
00:17:27,033 --> 00:17:28,733
He needs time
to cool off.

370
00:17:28,833 --> 00:17:29,933
Let's eat.

371
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:33,233
[LAUGHS]

372
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:35,633
We're having
ponyfish again for dinner?

373
00:17:35,767 --> 00:17:37,667
[SNIFFS] Mmm.

374
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:41,067
I think someone is missing
our old guest.

375
00:17:41,167 --> 00:17:42,400
[LAUGHS]

376
00:17:42,533 --> 00:17:44,467
I noticed you've been
cooking her favorite dish.

377
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:46,767
- Let's just eat.
- [CHUCKLES]

378
00:17:46,933 --> 00:17:48,300
Here's the spoon.

379
00:17:48,467 --> 00:17:51,433
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

380
00:17:57,800 --> 00:18:01,100
Girl, that's enough.
Take a break. Let's eat.

381
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:02,700
I need to finish this.

382
00:18:04,133 --> 00:18:05,767
Gosh, I told you,
Stephen.

383
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:08,933
She'll agree to come with us,
but she won't stop working.

384
00:18:09,033 --> 00:18:11,600
I'm hungry, like, for real.

385
00:18:11,733 --> 00:18:13,100
Caroline, come on,
take a break.

386
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,300
I can't.

387
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:17,267
At least take a bite.

388
00:18:19,067 --> 00:18:20,533
What's that about,
anyway?

389
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:24,333
Papa made us choose
a project we'd like to handle,

390
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,300
and I want to save
and continue this project

391
00:18:26,433 --> 00:18:29,133
wherein we provide housing
for abandoned kids.

392
00:18:29,267 --> 00:18:30,967
Well, that's a good idea.

393
00:18:31,667 --> 00:18:33,567
It will both help
those kids

394
00:18:33,700 --> 00:18:35,500
and the company's
image and branding.

395
00:18:35,667 --> 00:18:38,867
Yes, but the land we want to
acquire is owned by the Liaos.

396
00:18:41,167 --> 00:18:42,800
Then talk to your future
brother-in-law.

397
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:45,700
Edward?

398
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:49,033
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

399
00:18:49,167 --> 00:18:52,233
Wow! This food is so yummy.

400
00:18:52,367 --> 00:18:54,067
Sorry, I just finished fasting.

401
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:55,533
I'm really hungry.

402
00:18:57,700 --> 00:18:58,600
Mmm.

403
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:09,000
"Dinner with my
workaholic bestie."

404
00:19:09,133 --> 00:19:11,767
Now there's the Irene
I know.

405
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:15,667
It looks like you're
okay now.

406
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:17,433
I'm not okay!

407
00:19:17,567 --> 00:19:19,367
What's with the attitude?

408
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:23,533
That leech is so annoying!

409
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:26,333
Why? What did she do
this time?

410
00:19:26,433 --> 00:19:28,333
She's working overtime
at the office.

411
00:19:28,467 --> 00:19:30,733
Is she trying to prove
that she's a workaholic?

412
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:33,067
It's just going to make me
look bad.

413
00:19:33,233 --> 00:19:35,900
I'm just trying to respect
everyone's working hours.

414
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:38,433
You know what?

415
00:19:39,433 --> 00:19:42,467
Before getting yourself
a foot massage,

416
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:45,300
make sure to clear
your backlogs first.

417
00:19:45,433 --> 00:19:46,867
That's what you should do.

418
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:48,867
No.

419
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,367
Actually...

420
00:19:50,467 --> 00:19:51,767
You can stop now.

421
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:53,400
I'm going to the office.

422
00:19:53,567 --> 00:19:55,733
What? Are you crazy?

423
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:56,800
Yes.

424
00:19:58,333 --> 00:19:59,467
Okay, I knew that.

425
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,733
But no.
Just stay here.

426
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:04,133
It's late already.

427
00:20:04,267 --> 00:20:05,967
Just make it up
tomorrow.

428
00:20:06,933 --> 00:20:08,833
Be the last
to leave the office.

429
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:10,800
Okay?

430
00:20:15,367 --> 00:20:17,467
[BETTINA] Enjoy your massage.

431
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:24,833
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

432
00:20:24,967 --> 00:20:26,467
Thank you for the food.

433
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,900
No worries.
I mean, I ate all of it.

434
00:20:29,033 --> 00:20:30,300
[CHUCKLES] Alright then.

435
00:20:30,433 --> 00:20:32,000
- Bye.
- I'll see you.

436
00:20:32,133 --> 00:20:34,500
- I'll walk her to her car.
- Such a gentleman.

437
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:38,033
- Thank you.
- Bye.

438
00:20:38,167 --> 00:20:39,300
Take care.

439
00:20:39,467 --> 00:20:40,833
Bye!

440
00:20:42,300 --> 00:20:43,133
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

441
00:20:47,167 --> 00:20:48,167
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

442
00:20:48,300 --> 00:20:50,300
- [GROANS]
- [STOMACH GROWLING]

443
00:20:50,467 --> 00:20:52,433
Ma'am, are you still hungry?

444
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:56,000
Should I take you home?

445
00:20:58,333 --> 00:20:59,600
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

446
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:02,833
Oh, dear.
I bet that's Chairman.

447
00:21:02,967 --> 00:21:06,633
- It's fine. Don't worry.
- He'll eat our food again.

448
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:09,200
- I'll hide it.
- Hey, no.

449
00:21:09,367 --> 00:21:11,567
This is supposed
to last until tomorrow.

450
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:13,633
It's fine. This isn't
new anyway.

451
00:21:13,733 --> 00:21:15,467
Come in, Chairman.
Feel at home.

452
00:21:15,567 --> 00:21:17,133
- Come in.
- Grandma.

453
00:21:20,100 --> 00:21:21,333
[BOTH GASP]

454
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:24,200
- Ling!
- What a pleasant surprise!

455
00:21:24,333 --> 00:21:25,800
- What brings you here?
- Ling.

456
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:29,133
- It's nice to see you.
- [CHUCKLES]

457
00:21:29,267 --> 00:21:31,567
- How are you?
- Join us.

458
00:21:31,700 --> 00:21:33,900
What brings you here?

459
00:21:34,033 --> 00:21:35,467
Oh, I think I know why.

460
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:36,533
[STOMACH GROWLING]

461
00:21:36,667 --> 00:21:38,967
- There it is.
- [CHUCKLES]

462
00:21:39,067 --> 00:21:40,567
I heard that.

463
00:21:40,700 --> 00:21:43,200
- Me too.
- Someone is hungry.

464
00:21:43,367 --> 00:21:45,733
- Have a seat.
- I cooked your favorite.

465
00:21:45,867 --> 00:21:47,733
- Perfect timing.
- Let's eat.

466
00:21:47,867 --> 00:21:50,367
- Sit there.
- I thought it was Chairman.

467
00:21:50,533 --> 00:21:54,100
I'll get you some rice.
Eat up, okay?

468
00:21:54,233 --> 00:21:56,667
- [CHUCKLES]
- There you go.

469
00:21:56,767 --> 00:21:58,200
[MONCHING] You came
just in time.

470
00:21:58,367 --> 00:22:00,700
[NENE] Here you go.

471
00:22:01,933 --> 00:22:04,233
- It's your favorite, right?
- [MONCHING] Mmm.

472
00:22:04,367 --> 00:22:05,600
[PLATES, CUTLERY CLINKING]

473
00:22:05,733 --> 00:22:07,500
Is this the one
you cooked for me before?

474
00:22:07,633 --> 00:22:09,500
Yes. What do you
call that fish again?

475
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:11,400
I told you its name,
remember?

476
00:22:11,533 --> 00:22:12,833
What is it?

477
00:22:14,367 --> 00:22:15,933
- Um...
- It's ponyfish.

478
00:22:16,100 --> 00:22:18,567
- It's so yummy!
- [NENE] It's ponyfish.

479
00:22:18,733 --> 00:22:20,533
- Ponyfish stewed in vinegar.
- [NENE] Yes.

480
00:22:20,667 --> 00:22:22,033
It's your favorite, right?

481
00:22:22,167 --> 00:22:25,533
You eat it with fish sauce
and oil, remember?

482
00:22:25,633 --> 00:22:27,467
- Here.
- Eat up.

483
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:29,367
It's the best!

484
00:22:29,467 --> 00:22:31,467
I bet you'll feel
full later.

485
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:33,367
There. You're all set.

486
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:34,633
Eat up.

487
00:22:34,767 --> 00:22:37,933
You know, dear, you shouldn't
skip your meals.

488
00:22:38,067 --> 00:22:41,867
Make sure to always
eat on time, okay?

489
00:22:41,967 --> 00:22:45,367
I was busy with work
and felt a bit stressed out.

490
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:47,933
Oh, that makes sense.

491
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:50,400
You're just like Bingo.

492
00:22:50,500 --> 00:22:52,133
He's also stressed out.

493
00:22:52,267 --> 00:22:54,500
It's because his OPIP
proposal got rejected.

494
00:22:54,633 --> 00:22:55,933
[MONCHING] Mm-hmm.

495
00:22:56,100 --> 00:22:59,933
He should've called you
and talked to you.

496
00:23:01,433 --> 00:23:02,467
Um...

497
00:23:02,600 --> 00:23:06,567
I changed my number
for security reasons.

498
00:23:06,667 --> 00:23:09,567
- Oh, is that so?
- But...

499
00:23:12,633 --> 00:23:14,000
Here's my new number...

500
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:18,067
- in case you need to call me.
- Take it.

501
00:23:18,167 --> 00:23:19,967
Is that really it?

502
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:21,600
I doubt that.

503
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:24,467
You want us to call you what
we're having for dinner.

504
00:23:24,633 --> 00:23:25,600
[LAUGHTER]

505
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:27,433
Anyway, continue eating.

506
00:23:27,533 --> 00:23:29,333
Eat up, dear.

507
00:23:29,467 --> 00:23:31,167
I'll set this aside first.

508
00:23:31,300 --> 00:23:32,167
It's good, right?

509
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:36,433
You deserve an explanation.

510
00:23:36,567 --> 00:23:40,033
You deserve an
"accessible" reason.

511
00:23:40,167 --> 00:23:43,467
Silly! You mean "acceptable?"
[CHUCKLES]

512
00:23:43,633 --> 00:23:44,533
Oh.

513
00:23:44,667 --> 00:23:47,767
You deserve
an accessible reason.

514
00:23:47,867 --> 00:23:48,700
[LAUGHS]

515
00:23:48,833 --> 00:23:50,467
You just repeated it,
you idiot!

516
00:23:50,633 --> 00:23:53,333
[BOTH LAUGHING]

517
